Here's how to implement this in .NET MAUI Shell:

**1. Override `OnBackButtonPressed` and add a custom toolbar item:**

```csharp
public partial class EditProductPage : ContentPage
{
    private bool _hasUnsavedChanges;

    public EditProductPage()
    {
        InitializeComponent();

        // Hide default back button, add custom "Cancel" button
        Shell.SetBackButtonBehavior(this, new BackButtonBehavior
        {
            TextOverride = "Cancel",
            Command = new Command(async () => await TryNavigateBack())
        });
    }

    // Intercepts hardware/gesture back (Android back button, swipe)
    protected override bool OnBackButtonPressed()
    {
        if (_hasUnsavedChanges)
        {
            MainThread.BeginInvokeOnMainThread(async () => await TryNavigateBack());
            return true; // Cancel the default navigation
        }
        return base.OnBackButtonPressed();
    }

    private async Task TryNavigateBack()
    {
        if (_hasUnsavedChanges)
        {
            bool leave = await DisplayAlert(
                "Unsaved Changes",
                "You have unsaved changes. Discard and go back?",
                "Discard", "Stay");

            if (!leave)
                return; // User chose to stay
        }

        await Shell.Current.GoToAsync("..");
    }
}
```

**Key points:**

- **`BackButtonBehavior`** — replaces the shell back arrow with your "Cancel" text and routes taps through your logic.
- **`OnBackButtonPressed`** — catches Android hardware/gesture back; return `true` to cancel navigation.
- **iOS swipe-back gesture** — isn't caught by `OnBackButtonPressed`. Setting `BackButtonBehavior` disables the swipe gesture automatically on iOS. If you still need it, you can disable it explicitly:

```csharp
Shell.SetPresentationMode(this, PresentationMode.ModalAnimated);
// or on iOS, disable the interactive pop gesture in a custom renderer/handler
```

This gives you full control over back navigation with a confirmation prompt.
